when I told them I was leaving.

94
00:07:20,784 --> 00:07:23,703
- Miss DeVoto...
- I have a wonderful disposition.

95
00:07:23,787 --> 00:07:25,163
I put people right at ease.

96
00:07:25,247 --> 00:07:27,916
Miss DeVoto,
these people are already at ease.

97
00:07:28,834 --> 00:07:30,710
This is not a beauty parlor.

98
00:07:31,003 --> 00:07:32,712
It's a funeral parlor.

99
00:07:34,131 --> 00:07:35,298
They're dead?

100
00:07:35,591 --> 00:07:36,758
Yes, they are.

101
00:07:37,218 --> 00:07:38,510
Stiffs?

102
00:07:38,969 --> 00:07:40,345
Deceased.

103
00:07:41,096 --> 00:07:43,181
The ad just said makeup artist.

104
00:07:44,350 --> 00:07:45,433
Excuse me a second, will you?

105
00:07:45,935 --> 00:07:47,100
Sure.

106
00:07:48,853 --> 00:07:50,437
Hi, George.

107
00:07:50,605 --> 00:07:52,147
This is a 1258.

108
00:07:52,273 --> 00:07:54,399
I didn't want the burnished handles.

109
00:07:54,943 --> 00:07:57,069
- Is that your camper?
- Yes, it is.

110
00:07:57,153 --> 00:07:58,695
That's really cool.

111
00:08:01,282 --> 00:08:02,282
Hello.

112
00:08:03,785 --> 00:08:04,868
She's shy.

113
00:08:07,080 --> 00:08:09,122
Just put it back in
the display room, fellas.

114
00:08:09,207 --> 00:08:11,458
Okay, Harry.

115
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:16,213
Daddy, how come that coffin's so small?

116
00:08:16,881 --> 00:08:19,466
They come in all sizes,
honey, just like shoes.

117
00:08:19,884 --> 00:08:21,802
Is it for a child?

118
00:08:22,428 --> 00:08:23,470
Of course not.

119
00:08:23,555 --> 00:08:25,347
Then who's it for?

120
00:08:25,431 --> 00:08:27,599
Short people. Very short people.

121
00:08:27,684 --> 00:08:29,142
Excuse me.

122
00:08:29,644 --> 00:08:31,102
What about the job?

123
00:08:31,520 --> 00:08:33,020
Pardon?

124
00:08:33,105 --> 00:08:34,647
I need the job.

125
00:08:34,731 --> 00:08:37,233
You still want it, even though...

126
00:08:37,317 --> 00:08:39,735
Sure, it's no big deal.

127
00:08:39,820 --> 00:08:43,406
You see, all my former clients
will eventually die,

128
00:08:43,490 --> 00:08:45,825
and all your clients used to be alive.

129
00:08:45,951 --> 00:08:47,868
So they have something in common.

130
00:08:48,495 --> 00:08:51,038
You'd be doing hair and makeup
and answering the phone.

131
00:08:52,291 --> 00:08:54,125
Okay, Mr. Sultenfuss.

132
00:08:54,334 --> 00:08:56,043
- You've got a deal.
- Great.

133
00:08:56,461 --> 00:08:58,170
- You can start right away.
- Okay.

134
00:08:58,255 --> 00:08:59,589
Call me Harry.

135
00:09:00,007 --> 00:09:01,215
Now...

136
00:09:02,050 --> 00:09:04,927
Is this what
you'd normally wear for work or...

137
00:09:05,012 --> 00:09:06,637
- Look...
- Don't get me wrong.

138
00:09:06,722 --> 00:09:08,848
I like it very much, but the...

139
00:09:09,099 --> 00:09:11,726
I promise I'll take good
care of these people.

140
00:09:12,185 --> 00:09:13,810
They deserve it.

141
00:09:13,894 --> 00:09:15,020
They're dead.

142
00:09:16,522 --> 00:09:18,273
All they've got left is their looks.

143
00:09:34,540 --> 00:09:36,958
Hey, look at this. No feet.

144
00:09:37,043 --> 00:09:39,419
Wow, a real Evel Knievel.

145
00:09:50,556 --> 00:09:53,808
What the hell are you doing in my garage?
Get out of here!

146
00:10:24,005 --> 00:10:26,131
Hi, Vada, what's wrong today?

147
00:10:26,216 --> 00:10:27,424
I'm very sick.

148
00:10:27,926 --> 00:10:31,095
Okay, take a seat.
I'll check if the doctor can see you.

149
00:10:34,724 --> 00:10:37,601
Vada's here. She says she's very sick.

150
00:10:38,353 --> 00:10:39,769
She looks all right to me.

151
00:10:40,479 --> 00:10:43,564
Yeah. Yeah. Okay. He'll see you.

152
00:10:44,024 --> 00:10:45,775
Why don't you go in?

153
00:10:51,865 --> 00:10:54,659
Well, what is it? I can handle it.

154
00:10:54,952 --> 00:10:56,661
You are perfectly healthy.

155
00:10:56,912 --> 00:10:59,622
That can't be.
I have all the classic symptoms.

156
00:11:00,207 --> 00:11:02,458
Sweetheart, did they bring Mr. Layton
to your house today?

157
00:11:02,543 --> 00:11:03,543
Yes.

158
00:11:03,627 --> 00:11:07,880
Vada, you've got to stop this.
There's absolutely nothing wrong with you.

159
00:11:16,348 --> 00:11:18,683
I'll just have to get a second opinion.

160
00:11:24,313 --> 00:11:26,606
So what did he say was wrong with you?

161
00:11:27,358 --> 00:11:30,068
The whole medical profession is a crock.

162
00:11:30,361 --> 00:11:32,154
Hey, wait up for me.

163
00:11:49,338 --> 00:11:51,339
- Hey, look.
- At what?

164
00:11:51,716 --> 00:11:54,092
That's Mr. Bixler. Let's go talk to him.

165
00:11:54,177 --> 00:11:56,261
I don't want to talk to no teacher.
It's summer.

166
00:11:56,345 --> 00:11:57,471
Hi, Mr. Bixler.

167
00:11:58,097 --> 00:12:00,849
Mademoiselle Sultenfuss
and the amazing Dr. J.

168
00:12:00,933 --> 00:12:03,268
- How's the summer treating you?
- It's okay.

169
00:12:03,519 --> 00:12:06,896
Mr. Bixler, I finished all the books
for summer reading.

170
00:12:07,355 --> 00:12:09,940
Really? Already? The summer's just begun.

171
00:12:10,025 --> 00:12:12,526
Yes, and now I'm reading
War and Peace for fun.

172
00:12:12,944 --> 00:12:14,945
No wonder you're my prize pupil.

173
00:12:15,447 --> 00:12:18,365
- What about you, Thomas J?
- I haven't started yet.

174
00:12:18,533 --> 00:12:20,117
Better get on his case, Vada.

175
00:12:20,202 --> 00:12:22,661
Mr. Bixler, how come
you're painting this old house?

176
00:12:22,996 --> 00:12:25,539
Well, I just bought it.
Now I'm fixing it up.

177
00:12:26,792 --> 00:12:29,084
This is one big house for one single person.

178
00:12:30,003 --> 00:12:32,630
Well, you never can tell.

179
00:12:34,633 --> 00:12:35,716
I might get a pet.

180
00:12:36,968 --> 00:12:39,136
How are you going to get the money
to pay for this old house

181
00:12:39,221 --> 00:12:40,763
if you're not working?

182
00:12:40,847 --> 00:12:42,807
Well, I'm going to teach
creative writing this summer.

183
00:12:42,891 --> 00:12:45,267
So, I'm doing some work.

184
00:12:45,811 --> 00:12:48,646
- How much does it cost?
- $35.

185
00:12:48,730 --> 00:12:49,979
What do you get for that?

186
00:12:50,064 --> 00:12:52,899
Me, two hours a week, talking about poetry.

187
00:12:53,692 --> 00:12:56,277
- This an interrogation, Vada?
- No.

188
00:12:57,071 --> 00:13:00,073
Well, I guess I'll go home
and finish off War and Peace.

189
00:13:00,282 --> 00:13:03,535
It's summer. You're kids. Go play.

190
00:13:10,584 --> 00:13:13,169
Want to go to Gray's orchard
and pick some peaches?

191
00:13:13,254 --> 00:13:16,923
- No, I'm going home.
- Why? It's not dinnertime yet.

192
00:13:17,007 --> 00:13:20,677
"Dinnertime"? You're like a dog.
You just go home to eat!

193
00:13:20,761 --> 00:13:22,762
Don't pee on the hydrant!

194
00:13:42,511 --> 00:13:45,036
<i>Bill</i>

195
00:13:45,114 --> 00:13:50,108
