Rupert Gwynn called.
There was a big accident on PA-34.

201
00:14:08,725 --> 00:14:10,183
They're bringing in two tomorrow.

202
00:14:10,268 --> 00:14:13,103
Excuse me, Harry,
I finished Mr. Layton's hair.

203
00:14:13,187 --> 00:14:15,689
He kinda looked...
Harry, what's wrong with her?

204
00:14:15,773 --> 00:14:19,275
She's just pretending.
Vada, get up here and eat your broccoli.

205
00:14:20,485 --> 00:14:22,528
I think it's my prostate.

206
00:14:24,990 --> 00:14:28,075
No. How many removals
did you say we were expecting?

207
00:14:28,160 --> 00:14:29,368
Two. I'm gonna have
to do a v-section on one.

208
00:14:29,453 --> 00:14:30,578
Can you give me a hand?

209
00:14:30,662 --> 00:14:32,121
Well, I guess so. If you want.

210
00:14:32,205 --> 00:14:36,500
Now this isn't gonna be a repeat of that
smelter accident a few years ago, is it?

211
00:14:36,585 --> 00:14:39,170
Don't mock that.
That's how we bought the new Cadillac.

212
00:14:39,296 --> 00:14:42,089
Yes, I know that.
Except, I had a body in my bedroom,

213
00:14:42,174 --> 00:14:46,052
you had a body in your bedroom.
We were littered with peoples' bodies.

214
00:14:55,020 --> 00:14:56,604
- Who's winning?
- I am.

215
00:14:58,440 --> 00:15:00,732
Look. Vada and her little boyfriend.

216
00:15:01,359 --> 00:15:02,776
He is not my boyfriend.

217
00:15:02,902 --> 00:15:05,153
I bet she kisses him on the lips.

218
00:15:05,488 --> 00:15:07,238
Do you think I'd kiss that ugly old thing?

219
00:15:07,615 --> 00:15:09,074
Yeah, anyway.

220
00:15:09,867 --> 00:15:11,326
Come on, let's go.

221
00:15:11,410 --> 00:15:16,456
Judy's father owns the Bijou Theater,
and we get to see all the movies for free.

222
00:15:16,540 --> 00:15:19,292
- Maybe you can come sometime.
- Don't invite her.

223
00:15:19,377 --> 00:15:21,336
She'll have to bring her boyfriend.

224
00:15:22,041 --> 00:15:24,236
<i>Vada and Thomas</i>

225
00:15:24,310 --> 00:15:26,039
<i>Sittin' in a tree</i>

226
00:15:26,112 --> 00:15:29,980
<i>K - I - S - S - I - N - G</i>

227
00:15:30,049 --> 00:15:33,917
<i>First comes love
Then comes marriage</i>

228
00:15:33,986 --> 00:15:38,923
<i>Then comes Thomas J.
in the baby carriage</i>

229
00:15:39,271 --> 00:15:41,940
You know, Vada,
you shouldn't let those girls upset you.

230
00:15:42,233 --> 00:15:45,651
I'm not upset.
I will never play with those girls.

231
00:15:45,735 --> 00:15:49,655
I only surround myself with people
who I find intellectually stimulating.

232
00:15:55,203 --> 00:15:56,912
Want a piece of chocolate?

233
00:15:57,747 --> 00:16:00,207
- Thomas J?
- I'm allergic to it.

234
00:16:00,375 --> 00:16:02,793
- To chocolate?
- He's allergic to everything.

235
00:16:02,877 --> 00:16:03,877
To chocolate?

236
00:16:04,129 --> 00:16:05,838
- To everything.
- To everything.

237
00:16:08,758 --> 00:16:12,112
- That's a pretty ring you're wearing.
- It's a mood ring.

238
00:16:12,147 --> 00:16:15,286
- It tells what mood I'm in.
- It doesn't work. It always stays black.

239
00:16:15,616 --> 00:16:19,059
It's only black when you're around
'cause you put me in a bad mood.

240
00:16:19,519 --> 00:16:21,186
Maybe black means you're happy.

241
00:16:21,855 --> 00:16:23,480
I don't think so.

242
00:16:23,690 --> 00:16:25,898
Shelly, how can I get $35?

243
00:16:26,275 --> 00:16:28,943
She's crazy.
She wants to go to school over the summer.

244
00:16:29,278 --> 00:16:33,531
It's not a real school.
It's a writing class. I want to be a writer.

245
00:16:33,615 --> 00:16:36,159
She only wants to go
because her sweetie pie's the teacher.

246
00:16:36,410 --> 00:16:38,369
Shut your big fat mouth!

247
00:16:39,121 --> 00:16:41,122
I think you'd make a fine writer.

248
00:16:41,248 --> 00:16:42,832
Did you ask your dad?

249
00:16:43,167 --> 00:16:44,625
He won't give it to me.

250
00:16:44,960 --> 00:16:46,961
Well, you don't know that.

251
00:16:47,629 --> 00:16:48,838
